# React useRef Hook 

useRef is one of the most important React hooks. It helps you access DOM elements, store mutable values, and persist data across renders without causing re-renders.

---

1. What is useRef ?
useRef allows you to create a mutable reference that persists for the full lifetime of the component.

Key points:
          It stores a value in .current
          Updating .current does NOT cause re-render
          Commonly used for DOM access and storing values silently

const ref = useRef(initialValue);


Why use useRef?
2. Problems with useState:
            Triggers re-render on every update
            Not suitable for DOM access or timers

useRef solves this by:

Avoiding unnecessary re-renders
Allowing direct DOM manipulation
Persisting values between renders

................................................
 Example 2: Copy Text to Clipboard
import { useRef } from "react";

function App() {
  const inputRef = useRef();

  const copyText = () => {
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(inputRef.current.value);
    alert("Text Copied!");
  };

  return (
    <>
      <input ref={inputRef} type="text" placeholder="Type something" />
      <button onClick={copyText}>Copy</button>
    </>
  );
}

export default App;
